pesticide.PPE: All mixers, loaders, applicators, and other handlers must wear: long sleeved shirt and long pants; shoes plus socks; chemical resistant gloves, except for pilots; chemical resistant apron when mixing, loading, cleaning up spills, cleaning equipment, or otherwise exposed to the concentrate

Safety_Information.general_Info: HAZARDS TO HUMANS AND DOMESTIC ANIMALS CAUTION Harmful if swallowed or absorbed through skin. Avoid contact with skin, eyes or clothing. Harmful if inhaled. Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid breathing spray mist or vapor. Do not take alcohol immediately before or after exposure to this product. The consumption of alcohol by the applicator can increase the toxicity of the product. Prolonged or frequently repeated skin contact may cause allergic reactions in some individuals. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet. Remove and wash contaminated clothing before reuse.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Inhaled: Move person to fresh air. If person is not breathing, call 911 or an ambulance, then give artificial respiration, preferably by mouth-to-mouth, if possible. Call a poison control center or doctor for further treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or going for treatment.

Application_Info.units: quart of product per 7 quarts of water per 1000 square feet
